<br>
(lvl 44 spells)<br>
Boon of Garou + Elemental Maelestrom + Corporal Empathy + Enticement of Flame = A note you turn BACK into the quest giver and he gives you Item 1<br>
<br>
(lvl 50 spells)<br>
Invis to Undead + translocate + Monster Summ 2 + Improved Invis = A note you turn BACK into the quest giver and he gives you Item 2<br>
<br>
(lvl 51 spells)<br>
Theft of Thought + Splurt + Gift of Xev + Atol's Spectral Shackles = A note you turn BACK into the quest giver and he gives you Item 3<br>
<br>
No damn clue what equals Item 4 which seems to be the last item we need boo. if you turn in the items to the quest apprentice guys, they only give you a cash item and faction so that is not the right track either I do not think.<br>
<br>
It seems that only spells between 39 and 51 work (so 39, 44, 49, 50, 51) but why 5 circles if we only need 4 items? Anyway, it ALSO seems that only Vel/Kunark dropped spells work, but here is the flaw:<br>
<br>
Lvl 39 spells (dropped) are Wandering Mind + Chilling Embrace + invis to Undead + there IS NO mage dropped lvl 39 spell.<br>
<br>
Lvl 49 is even worse as only ONE spell from all 4 classes is dropped and it is Dead MEN Floating and we all know how rare that is. So what to do? I have compared casting times, mana costs, even schools of magic for each spell and lvl and cannot seem to come up with a way to link the spells together. (Oh BTW I am 100% sure the preceeding combines work as I did them all before servers went down.) I think if we find the common thread here we can figure this quest out. <br>
<br>
Oh and Rhion the quest text you wrote down involves handing in old Apothic armor to the gnome, apparently you receive a rare gem of some sort and some XP, so yay for us who never let Apothic rot (I have 8 pieces in bank I can't wait to try out even a spare robe).  Oh and also YES you need a high research skill (mine is near 180) if it is too low you get a message that says in essence &quot;You suck skill up first dork&quot;  *grin*  <br>
As for the ideas about going to other sages, I think that is incorrect. I cannot explain why exactly, but my gut tells me the new spell quest (this one) involves just this guy. The other sages each have their OWN ways of doing things it seems, so in essence, we have FOUR ways to get new spells. <br>
<br>
1) Combining old spells (this thread's subject)<br>
2) Combining new words and runes.<br>
3) Combining new items with charges of the spells together to get the spells.<br>
4) Turning in Ethereal parchment drops (currently the ONLY way to get the new spells for SURE)<br>
<br>
I think that covers anything, I will be watching this thread today closely until servers come back up, cmon guys I know we got some smarties in here so let sget cracking.<br>
<br>
Baervon<br>
